{"review": [{"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 0, "sentence": "[Summary]:"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 1, "sentence": "This paper tackles the problem of automatic robot design."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 2, "sentence": "The most popular approach to doing this has been evolutionary methods which work by evolving morphology of agents in a feed-forward manner using a propagation and mutation rules."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 3, "sentence": "This is a non-differentiable process and relies on maintaining a large pool of candidates out of which best ones are chosen with the highest fitness."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 4, "sentence": "In robot design for a given task using rewards, training each robot design using RL with rewards is an expensive process and not scalable."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 5, "sentence": "This paper uses graph network to train each morphology using RL."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 6, "sentence": "Thereby, allowing the controller to share parameters and reuse information across generations."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 7, "sentence": "This expedites the score function evaluation improving the time complexity of the evolutionary process."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 8, "sentence": "[Strengths]:"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 9, "sentence": "This paper shows some promise when graph network-based controllers augmented with evolutionary algorithms."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 10, "sentence": "Paper is quite easy to follow."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 11, "sentence": "[Weaknesses and Clarifications]:"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 12, "sentence": "=> Robot design area has been explored extensively in classical work of Sims (1994) etc. using ES."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 13, "sentence": "Given that, the novelty of the paper is fairly incremental as it uses NerveNet to evaluate fitness and ES for the main design search."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 14, "sentence": "=> Environment: The experimental section of the paper can be further improved."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 15, "sentence": "The approach is evaluated only in three cases: fish, walker, cheetah. Can it be applied to more complex morphologies? Humanoid etc. maybe?"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 16, "sentence": "=> Baselines: The comparison provided in the paper is weak."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 17, "sentence": "At first, it compares to random graph search and ES."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 18, "sentence": "But there are better baselines possible."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 19, "sentence": "One such example would be to have a network for each body part and share parameters across each body part."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 20, "sentence": "This network takes some identifying information (ID, shape etc.) about body part as input."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 21, "sentence": "As more body parts are added, more such network modules can be added."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 22, "sentence": "How would the given graph network compare to this?"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 23, "sentence": "This baseline can be thought of a shared parameter graph with no message passing."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 24, "sentence": "=> The results shown in Figure-4 (Section-4.2) seems unclear to me."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 25, "sentence": "As far as I understand, the model starts with hand-engineered design and then finetuned using evolutionary process."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 26, "sentence": "However, the original performance of the hand-engineered design is surprisingly bad (see first data point in any plot in Figure-4)."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 27, "sentence": "Does the controller also start from scratch? If so, why? Also, it is not clear what is the meaning of generations if the graph is fixed, can't it be learned altogether at once?"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 28, "sentence": "[Recommendation]:"}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 29, "sentence": "I request the authors to address the comments raised above."}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 30, "sentence": "Overall, this is a reasonable paper but experimental section needs much more attention."}], "reviewlabels": [{"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 0, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 1, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 2, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 3, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 4, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 5, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 6, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 7, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 8, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 9, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Motivation/Impact", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 10, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "P-Positive"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 11, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 12, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 13, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Originality", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 14, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Experiment", "asp": "Substance", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 15, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Experiment", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "U-Neutral"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 16, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Meaningful Comparison", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 17, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Quote", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 18, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Meaningful Comparison", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 19, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 20, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 21, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 22, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Explanation", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 23, "labels": {"coarse": "Fact", "fine": "Fact", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 24, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Clarity", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 25, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Summary", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 26, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 27, "labels": {"coarse": "Request", "fine": "Request.Explanation", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 28, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Heading", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 29, "labels": {"coarse": "Structuring", "fine": "Structuring.Quote", "asp": "", "pol": ""}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}, {"text_id": "rJxUPOqhhX", "sid": 30, "labels": {"coarse": "Evaluative", "fine": "Evaluative", "asp": "Soundness/Correctness", "pol": "N-Negative"}, "secondarylabels": [], "merge-with-prior": false}], "rebuttal": [{"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 0, "sentence": "We thank the reviewer for the suggestions."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 1, "sentence": "Q1: Robot design were explored in (Sims, 1994) etc. The novelty of the paper is fairly incremental."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 2, "sentence": "We respectfully disagree and believe our contributions are significant."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 3, "sentence": "We note that only NGE among all the baselines has the ability to optimize both the graph G and the controller parameters."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 4, "sentence": "Graph neural network formulation is KEY here, enabling it to perform this efficient policy transfer."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 5, "sentence": "To the best of our knowledge, the traditional methods (such as (Sims, 1994)) require re-optimizing parameters of the controllers from scratch for each different topologies, which is computationally demanding and breaks the joint-optimization."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 6, "sentence": "To further showcase our work with respect to prior art, we added (Sims, 1994) as an additional baseline in the latest revision."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 7, "sentence": "We refer the reviewer to the general response for details."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 8, "sentence": "NGE has about 2x performance of (Sims, 1994) in both fish and walker environments."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 9, "sentence": "Moreover, we argue the videos of (Sims, 1994) might be confusing as it mixes the results of policy evolution from human-designed robots and structure evolution."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 10, "sentence": "Q2: Can it be applied to more complex morphologies?"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 11, "sentence": "Humanoid etc."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 12, "sentence": "maybe?"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 13, "sentence": "NGE can be applied to evolve humanoids, however, there are two major difficulties in doing that in practice."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 14, "sentence": "1. Training humanoid controllers is of orders of magnitude more difficult than training cheetah (Schulman, 2017)."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 15, "sentence": "2. To evolve realistic humanoid structure (e.g. hands, symmetrical limbs), one would need to have more realistic environments that better reflect tasks and complexity in the real world."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 16, "sentence": "However, we agree that this is a very interesting direction for the future."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 17, "sentence": "Q3: Comparison to more baseline, for example models with no message passing."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 18, "sentence": "We thank the reviewer for pointing out the baseline of no message passing in GNN, which we named as ESS-BodyShare."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 19, "sentence": "In the latest revision, we have 5 baselines from previous research and modern variants, which further showcases the significance of our work."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 20, "sentence": "In general, NGE has significant improvement both quantitatively and qualitatively."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 21, "sentence": "We refer the reviewer to the general response for further information."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 22, "sentence": "Specifically for ESS-BodyShare baseline:"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 23, "sentence": "|"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 24, "sentence": "NGE     | ESS-BodyShare"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 25, "sentence": "fish         |  70.21   |  54.97"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 26, "sentence": "(78.3% of NGE)"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 27, "sentence": "Walker   |"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 28, "sentence": "4157.9 |   2185.1 (52.5% of NGE)"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 29, "sentence": "In environment where global information is needed (for example, walker with multiple rigid body contact), the performance is jeopardized. But in an easier environment, message passing is less needed."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 30, "sentence": "Q4: Clarification of Figure-4 (Section-4.2)"}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 31, "sentence": "Our aim was to show that in the case where the human-engineered topology needs to be preserved, it is better to co-evolve the attributes and controllers with NGE rather than only training the controllers (controllers are trained from scratch for both NGE and baselines)."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 32, "sentence": "The x-axis was scaled according to the number of updates."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 33, "sentence": "We apologize for the lack of clarity."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 34, "sentence": "We revised the x-axis from \u201cgenerations\u201d to parameter \u201cupdates\u201d in the latest revision."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 35, "sentence": "In the latest revision, we also included the curve where the topologies are allowed to be changed, which leads to better performance, but does not necessarily preserve the initial structure."}, {"text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 36, "sentence": "Schulman, 2017. \"Proximal policy optimization algorithms.\" arXiv preprint arXiv:1707.06347 (2017)."}], "rebuttallabels": [{"labels": {"alignments": [], "responsetype": "social", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 0}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 1}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "reject-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 2}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "reject-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 3}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "reject-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 4}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "reject-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 5}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "reject-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 6}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 7}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 8}, {"labels": {"alignments": [12, 13], "responsetype": "reject-criticism", "coarseresponse": "dispute"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 9}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 10}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 11}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 12}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 13}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 14}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 15}, {"labels": {"alignments": [14, 15], "responsetype": "future", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 16}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 17}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "concede-criticism", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 18}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "done_manu_Yes", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 19}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 20}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 21}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 22}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 23}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 24}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 25}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 26}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 27}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "summary", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 28}, {"labels": {"alignments": [16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 29}, {"labels": {"alignments": [24, 25, 26, 27], "responsetype": "structuring", "coarseresponse": "nonarg"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 30}, {"labels": {"alignments": [24, 25, 26, 27], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 31}, {"labels": {"alignments": [24, 25, 26, 27], "responsetype": "answer", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 32}, {"labels": {"alignments": [24, 25, 26, 27], "responsetype": "concede-criticism", "coarseresponse": "concur"}, "text_id": "BkeBMdpg07", "sid": 33}, 